episodes.title: Democrat Ro Khanna reveals six men's names in Epstein files
episodes.description:
The Democratic congressman Ro Khanna read out the names of six wealthy men included in the Jeffrey Epstein files. 
Subscribe to Guardian News on YouTube ► https://www.youtube.com/user/guardianwires?sub_confirmation=1

In a post on X at lunchtime, Khanna, of California, named the six as Salvatore Nuara, Zurab Mikeladze, Leonic Leonov, Nicola Caputo, Sultan Ahmed Bin Sulayem and Leslie Wexner. He said he and his Republican colleague Thomas Massie had forced the Department of Justice to disclose the 'hidden' names. 
 
Reading the names in the House of Representatives, Khanna availed himself of protection from any defamation lawsuit by the speech and debate clause of the US constitution.

episodes.title: 'Puzzling, inexplicable redactions': Jamie Raskin questions DoJ after viewing Epstein files
episodes.description:
Jamie Raskin, a top House Democrat, accused the justice department of making 'puzzling, inexplicable redactions' to documents related to Jeffrey Epstein that obscured the names of abusers, while allowing the identities of the disgraced financier’s victims to become public.
Subscribe to Guardian News on YouTube ► https://www.youtube.com/user/guardianwires?sub_confirmation=1

Raskin told reporters that he wanted to view the complete files to better understand how the justice department handled the redaction process.

episodes.title: Epstein associate Ghislaine Maxwell declines to answer questions before Congress
episodes.description:
Maxwell invoked the fifth amendment of the US constitution, granting her right to remain silent, as she appeared at a US congressional hearing on Monday.
Subscribe to Guardian News on YouTube ► https://www.youtube.com/user/guardianwires?sub_confirmation=1

After the hearing, the House representative for New Mexico Melanie Stansbury said the Epstein associate was 'campaigning for clemency' after her attorney, David Markus, said Maxwell was 'prepared to speak fully and honestly if granted clemency'. The US Department of Justice released millions of internal documents related to Epstein last month

episodes.title: Footage of Melbourne principal fighting extradition in Israel shows 'healthy' person
episodes.description: An Israeli court previously ruled that an alleged Australian sex abuser Malka Leifer was mentally unfit to be extradited to Australia to face 74 counts of suspected sexual abuse and rape from 2008, when she was principal of a Jewish ultra-orthodox girls school in Melbourne. An Israeli private investigator has been covertly filming Leifer in Israel and has built a case that he claims proves she is a 'normal, healthy person'.
